When building Sky1 PCIe with clang and strict warning settings
(`CONFIG_WERROR=y`, `W=1`), config-dependent paths fail with:

 - `-Wsometimes-uninitialized` in PCIe RC/ACPI helpers
 - `-Wunused-but-set-variable` in clock parsing
 - `-Wmissing-prototypes` and `-Wsometimes-uninitialized` in debugfs tests
 - `-Wunused-function` in !PM_SLEEP builds

Fixes:

 - Remove unused `ret` bookkeeping in clock parsing
 - Initialize error return in ACPI host-bridge init fallback path
 - Guard PHY status base pointer before use
 - Guard suspend-only helper functions with `#ifdef CONFIG_PM_SLEEP`
 - Guard ACPI fallback binding in probe with `#ifdef CONFIG_ACPI`
 - Mark local debugfs test helpers `static`
 - Initialize debugfs link-speed string default

This keeps Sky1 PCIe paths warning-clean under clang without changing
runtime behavior.

---
